    h2 About Kno U Kno
    p
      Kno U Kno is a practical study and coaching companion for founders, small-business leaders, and anyone building a commercial venture. We distill the messy, day-to-day decisions of starting and running a business into clear, focused questions you can answer in minutes — questions that prompt action, sharpen judgment, and create a record of learning you can revisit and refine.

    p
      The site is organized around three core areas: starting, managing, and money. Each area contains carefully chosen prompts and short examples that push you from abstract idea to concrete next step. Rather than long essays or generic checklists, we give you measured, practical questions that highlight the choices that matter at each stage — from defining a simple offering and testing early demand, to structuring your team, to setting sustainable pricing and tracking cash flow.

    p
      Our goal is to make thinking about your business routine, repeatable, and honest. Answering a question here should take less time than a coffee break, but yield outsized clarity. By answering regularly you build a documented trail of decisions and experiments: what you tried, why you chose it, what happened, and what you learned. That trail becomes a valuable resource when you need to explain your reasoning to partners, advisors, or potential investors — and it also surfaces small patterns you can iterate on.

    h3 Who this is for
    p
      Kno U Kno is aimed at founders, early-stage teams, independent consultants, and owner-operators who prefer fast, practical tools over long theory. If you’re starting a side project, launching a first product, or running a service business, these prompts help you prioritize the questions that move the business forward. They are intentionally actionable: many include short examples or micro-tasks you can run in the next week.

    h3 What you get
    ul
      li A large, searchable set of short, focused questions (organized into Start, Manage, and Money sections).
      li Practical examples and short exercises that clarify how a question maps to real work.
      li A private workspace to write and save your answers, track progress, and return to earlier experiments.
      li Tools for getting feedback — you can save answers, request grading, or invite collaborators to review and rate your thinking.
      li Simple membership tiers that expand access and let you track more answers or unlock collections of advanced prompts.

    h3 How to use it
    p
      Start with a single section that matches your immediate need. If you’re launching, begin with the Start questions to articulate a simple offer and pick a small experiment. If you’re growing operations, browse the Manage prompts to surface priorities around hiring, delegation, and customer experience. For cash and pricing questions, the Money section focuses on units, margins, pricing tests, and basic cash-management exercises.

    p
      Pick a question, read the short example, and write a short answer — one or two paragraphs or a checklist of next steps. Save the answer for later, and use the rating and grading features if you want feedback. Repeat weekly: answers add up, and you’ll find the patterns that deserve more attention.

    h3 Our approach to privacy and collaboration
    p
      Your answers are private by default. You can save and export your work, or use light-sharing controls to invite a mentor or team member to review specific answers. We don’t sell your responses — the product is built to help you make better decisions, not to mine your data.

    h3 Why questions, not long guides
    p
      Long articles and checklists have their place, but they often leave you unsure how to act. Questions force a decision: they isolate the uncertainty you should resolve today and direct you toward the smallest useful experiment. That minimalist approach keeps the focus on action, not perfection.

    h3 Next steps
    p
      Try answering one question now. Use the quick links to jump to milestone prompts like Question 50, 75, or 100 — each is selected to move your thinking forward in different ways. If you want more structure, consider a membership tier to unlock extended prompts, additional saves, and batch features.

    p.small
      Built with practical founders in mind. If you have ideas, questions, or requests, reach out — we read every thoughtful message and use that feedback to make the site more useful.
